      "message": "Yeah, I noticed that after I uploaded 😄. \n\nIt should be fine because the `nocrt\u003d\u003dTrue` toolchains are registered under a different toolchain type than the `nocrt\u003d\u003dFalse` toolchains: https://cs.android.com/android/platform/superproject/+/master:prebuilts/clang/host/linux-x86/cc_toolchain_config.bzl;l\u003d488;drc\u003d264929fc1d21a3041cc950841b4e43c7cd662d14. So the ordering for `nocrt\u003dTrue` vs `nocrt\u003dFalse` shouldn\u0027t matter as long as `tn(a1, v1, nocrt1)` comes before `_tn(a1, None, nocrt1)`.\n\nI just didn\u0027t want to have to restart presubmits, but it may be best to just upload a new patchset and keep it as it was before.",
